records.addlTxt:
09:34 AM Defendant Justin Scott Schwartz in court with attorney J Andrew Herbers.  Charles Patrick Hoffmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for plea and sentencing. 
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a no contest plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.
State and Defense makes sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

Court orders the following:
IMPOSED AND STAYED: 

JAIL:  90 Days in the Waukesha County Jail w/Huber (all standard release conditions).
1  Day Credit.

TERM ON PROBATION:  15 MONTHS; 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*Obtain GED;
*No violent contact with:  any witnesses or victim in the criminal complaint; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State-certified batterers intervention program;
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate;

COSTS:  $243
DOMESTIC VIOLENCE SURCHARGE: $100
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation.
